This is Rhys, a Steam compatibility tool that runs XNA games with FNA, using
XnaToFna to fix up various Windows-dependent features found in XNA games.

Runtime Dependencies
--------------------
- Mono 5.20 or older (6.0+ is missing MONO_IOMAP)

Build Dependencies
------------------
- NuGet
- Roslyn
- MSBuild

How to Build
------------
Run ./build.sh!

Why "Rhys"?
-----------
Rhys was the name of Shawn Hargreaves' cat. Shawn Hargreaves was the lead
developer of XNA, and his cat was frequently used in the official XNA examples.
